caption.title: Relative contributions the generation interval (blue) and the basic reproduction number R 0 (orange) to temperature-driven changes in epidemic growth rate r under different values of λ.
caption.p: Temperature changes are considered in 0.1°C increments. Varying the mosquito emergence rate λ made little difference in the overall contribution of the generation interval and reproduction numbers. For lower values of λ, the contribution of the generation interval is more pronounced due to an overall lower R 0. Values of λ considered here correspond to peak R 0 values of 0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 6.0, and 8.0, respectively.
